  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN134.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">viṉaimuṟṟi maṟuttarā mīṇṭa talaimakaṉ ṟērpākaṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What HE who returned without arguing after having completed the work said to the charioteer.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN134.2">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>vāṉam vāyppak kaviṉik kāṉaṅ</l>
                <l>kamañcūṉ māmaḻaik kārpayan tiṟutteṉa</l>
                <l>maṇimalarp pūvai yaṇimala riṭaiyiṭaic</l>
                <l>cempula mūtāy parattali ṉaṉpala</l>
                <l>mullai vīkaḻa ṟāay valalōṉ</l>
                <l>ceykai yaṉṉa cennilaip puṟaviṉ</l>
                <l>vāap pāṇi vayaṅkutoḻiṟ kalimāt</l>
                <l>tāat tāḷiṇai mella votuṅka</l>
                <l>viṭimaṟan tēmati valava kuvimukai</l>
                <l>vāḻai vāṉpū vūḻuṟu putirnta</l>
                <l>voḻikulai yaṉṉa tirimarup pēṟṟoṭu</l>
                <l>kaṇaikkā lampiṇaik kāmar puṇarnilaik</l>
                <l>kaṭumāṉ ṟēroli kēṭpi</l>
                <l>ṉaṭunāṭ kūṭṭa mākalu muṇṭē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>In the woodland in a state as red as the work</l>
                <l>of an expert, when jasmine blossoms become loose [and] spread, (5f.)</l>
                <l>a good many, because of the spreading of cochineals in the red fields,</l>
                <l>right among the decorative blossoms of the sapphire-blooming bilberry,</l>
                <l>since fully pregnant dark clouds tarried over the forest,</l>
                <l>as the rainy season produced [them], being beautiful as they gather in the sky, (1-4)</l>
                <l>forget the thunder [and] go, charioteer, (9a-c)</l>
                <l>while the pair with galloping legs tread softly,</l>
                <l>the spirited horses whose glowing task is a leaping rhythm. (7f.)</l>
                <l>When the round-legged pretty doe, in a desirable state of union</l>
                <l>with [her] stag with horns twisted like the bunches that remain</l>
                <l>when, at [their] turn, the pure flowers of the plantain with piling buds dropped off,</l>
                <l>hears the sound of the chariot with fast horses, (9d-13)</l>
                <l>[our] midnight meeting is to take place, too. (14)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
